## Traps

- **PyPI index-cache lag**: after publish, `uv pip install` may 404 the new version for a
  few min while the CDN propagates; the PyPI JSON API (`/pypi/<pkg>/json`) reflects sooner.
  Verify with `--refresh` and retry.
- **cwd shadowing on import smoke-tests**: `/tmp` has stray `enum.py`/`re`-shadowing `.py`
  files → `AttributeError: partially initialized module 're'`. Run import checks from a
  CLEAN empty dir, never `/tmp`.
- **Duplicate `pull_request`/`push` CI runs** race (`cancel-in-progress`): a check can show
  CANCELLED/timeout on the superseded run while the live run passes on the SAME SHA. Pin the
  head SHA, confirm the live run. main has NO required status-check contexts (`[]`) — merge is
  review-gated → owner `--admin`.
- **PACT job 5-min action-timeout** flakes on a slow runner (the suite runs ~5min); re-run
  the job. Local PACT needs `KAIZEN_DEFAULT_MODEL` set (not in `.env`; CI provisions it) —
  11 local failures are this env class, green on CI.
- **`tests/unit/observability/test_metrics_collector.py::test_metrics_overhead_is_minimal`**
  — absolute wall-clock ratio assertion, flakes under concurrent-suite load; green isolated.
  Pre-existing (no benchmark marker → not deselected). Not shard-introduced.
- **Shared review worktrees are a trap**: pointing a read-only reviewer + a Bash-capable
  reviewer at ONE `/tmp/wt-*` worktree let the code-reviewer's neutralization probe mutate
  it → the security-reviewer read the mutated tree and raised a false "guard un-wired"
  CRITICAL. Verify contested claims against the COMMITTED blob (`git show <sha>:<path>`).
- venv shebangs are STALE — always `.venv/bin/python -m <tool>`, never bare `pytest`.
